&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-family: Verdana;font-size: 12.0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Someone could set up a private email group server for us. I used to do this in the past, but have no desire to do it these days.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Something like:&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://list.org/&quot;&gt;https://list.org/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;If someone is willing to secure a small server for this, like an instance on AWS or similar, I can set it up, but don&#39;t wish to maintain it.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Here&#39;s a possible service, which is offering assistance for YahooGroup migration:&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://gaggle.email/&quot;&gt;https://gaggle.email/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;and&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://gaggle.email/blog/how-to-save-your-yahoo-groups-message-archive/&quot;&gt;https://gaggle.email/blog/how-to-save-your-yahoo-groups-message-archive/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Gaggle mail is not free, though. They will give you a free trial for 14 days.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;There is also&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.emaildodo.com/&quot;&gt;https://www.emaildodo.com/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Note that I have no experience with either of these email group services.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;signature&quot;&gt;Mit freundlichen Gr&uuml;&szlig;en&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Fred Mitchell&lt;/div&gt;

